The <strong><code>PerformanceResourceTiming</code></strong> interface enables retrieval and analysis of detailed network timing data regarding the loading of an application's <em>resources</em>. An application can use the timing metrics to determine, for example, the length of time it takes to fetch a specific resource, such as an <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLHttpRequest" title="Use XMLHttpRequest (XHR) objects to interact with servers. You can retrieve data from a URL without having to do a full page refresh. This enables a Web page to update just part of a page without disrupting what the user is doing."><code>XMLHttpRequest</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Element/SVG" title="The svg element is a container that defines a new coordinate system and viewport. It is used as the outermost element of any SVG document but it can also be used to embed a SVG fragment inside any SVG or HTML document."><code>&lt;SVG&gt;</code></a>, image, or script.